{meta: title The Life They Live In Song}
{meta: artist Kitty Wells}
{meta: writer Raymond F. Scrivner}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[G]All the songs they sing these day are [C]about the trifling [G]ways
[D7]Of the boys and girls who love in our hometown
[G]In my heart I have no fear when I [C]think of you my [G]dear
[D7]For I know that you will never slip [G]around
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
[C]There are back street affairs and hearts that need [G]repair
[D7]And it seems that love has always turned out wrong
[G]But I'll trust the love you [C]give darling you could never [G]live
[D7]The worthless kind of life they live in [G]song
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
[C]When a foolish love goes wrong someone always writes a [G]song
[D7]About the wildest side of life a soul can lead
[G]I'm so thankful dear for you cause [C]I'm sure you heart is [G]true
[D7]And no trifling song could ever plant the [G]seed
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
[C]When a heart goes astray and falls beside the [G]way
[D7]Let him find a love like ours to make him strong
[G]Always keep your trust in me and [C]your love will keep me [G]free
[D7]From the worthless kind of life they live in [G]song
{end_of_verse}

